Koninkrijk","of Sawbridgeworth, Herts., Eng.":"Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"ca. 1209–1228":"about 1209–1228","1209–1228":"1209–1228","1200–1228":"1200–1228","1225–Female":"1225–Deceased","1228–1277":"1228–1277","1162–1222":"1162–1222","1166–1242":"1166–1242","1242":"1242","1162":"1162","Bef 1228":"before 1228","1228":"1228","ca. 1209":"about 1209","1225":"1225","1222":"1222","1277":"1277","1200":"1200","1166":"1166","ABT. 1225":"about 1225","1209":"1209","26 February 1222":"26 February 1222","Hyde Hall, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England":"Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Hyde Hall, Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England":"Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom","Hertfordshire, England":"Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom","of Sawbridgeworth, Herts., Eng.":"Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Sudley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Sunley Hill in Kirkdale (North Yorkshire). The placename derives from the Old Norse personal name <i>Sunnólfr</i> + Old Norse <i>haugr</i> ‘hill, mound’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Elizabeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual spelling of   Elisabeth   in English. It is recorded in the medieval period, but was made popular by being borne by  Queen Elizabeth I  of England (  1533–1603 ). In the 20th century it again became extremely fashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Elizabeth Sudley was born about 1209, in Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, John Sudeley, was 48 and her mother, Isabel Stafford, was 44. She married John de Hyde in 1225, in Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. She died in 1228, in Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 20."},"et":{"ca. 1209–1228":"umbes 1209–1228","1209–1228":"1209–1228","1200–1228":"1200–1228","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","1228–1277":"1228–1277","1162–1222":"1162–1222","1166–1242":"1166–1242","1242":"1242","1162":"1162","Bef 1228":"enne 1228","1228":"1228","ca. 1209":"umbes 1209","1225":"1225","1222":"1222","1277":"1277","1200":"1200","1166":"1166","ABT. 1225":"umbes 1225","1209":"1209","26 February 1222":"26. veebruar 1222","Hyde Hall, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England":"Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hyde Hall, Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England":"Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hertfordshire, England":"Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Sawbridgeworth, Herts., Eng.":"Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ca. 1209–1228":"noin 1209–1228","1209–1228":"1209–1228","1200–1228":"1200–1228","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","1228–1277":"1228–1277","1162–1222":"1162–1222","116